                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/2–1346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in China</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-20T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 20, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>328. For General Marshall from Colonel Davis: The following from Treasury (Urtel
                    285, February 13, and Ourtel 298, February 15): <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <list>
                            <item>“1. War and Navy Departments estimate total yuan obligations for
                                1945 CN $104 billion. This figure does not include Chinese
                                expenditures on behalf of Army for board and lodging.</item>
                            <item>2. Treasury believes that range of US $125 to 150 million for CN
                                $104 billion would serve as adequate guide for General Marshall’s
                                negotiations.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Treasury is sending telegram<note n="80" xml:id="d665fn80">Department’s telegram
                        No. 373, February 28, 7 p.m., not printed.</note> to Adler on same subject.
                    [Davis.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
